         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 24/1/71 ¶  ¶ I am glad to hear, dear Dr Hooker, that you are proceeding so well with the genera. ¶  When you will have done the Rubiaceae and Mr Bentham the Compositae, there will be less ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.01.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, ff. 4-5.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/1/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad to hear, dear Dr Hooker, that you are proceeding so well with the genera.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83). See J. Hooker to M, 13 November 1870.</p>
               </note> When you will have done the <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name> and Mr Bentham the <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name>, there will be less difficulty, as the later orders of D.C.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A. P. de Candolle (1823-73).</p>
               </note> are resting on generic characters better worked out.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad to know we have <name key="Coffea%20Benghalensis">Coffea Benghalensis</name> in Australia.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Hooker to M, 13 November 1870.</p>
               </note> In a few years we will have a capital supplemental material for the Flora,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78).</p>
               </note> and new phanerogamic species will then hardly be left to be discovered. Indeed even now Dallachy can scarcely ever find anything new in N. E. Australia.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My difficulties here are not yet overcome. God knows where it will end. You have no idea of the meanness and lowness, existing in Victoria, among much of people of really highly principle. I think really the share of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bad people of influence</hi>
               </seg> is here far greater then in most other countries.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sure, Prof Oliver will gladly take notice of the huge <name key="Eucalyptus%20amygdalina">Eucalyptus amygdalina</name>; it being the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">tallest tree</hi>
               </seg> in her Majestys whole empire, European or colonial anywhere. Surely thus far it is worth mentioning in a suitable English publication.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad we are to get the rose-wood plant (<name key="Convolvulus%20scoparius">Convolvulus scoparius</name>)<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Hooker to M, 13 November 1870.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Poor Anderson! How soon he passed away! Overworked and worried.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Thomas Anderson died aged 38 in Edinburgh on 26 October 1870.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">What a very sad loss that of poor Prof Anderson. Yet so young, and so clever, and so excellent. How will his poor father get over it? I suppose the poor Gentleman overworked himself, which we are all apt to do.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A lecture of mine is just under press but it will not be ready to send it you til next mail.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The postscript is written on a separate sheet. It is assumed to belong with this letter from its sequence in the guard book, although it would also fit with M to J. Hooker, 5 January 1871. The lecture referred to is probably B71.04.03 which was delivered on 3 November 1870 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 4 November 1870, p. 5).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Coffea%20Benghalensis">Coffea Benghalensis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Convolvulus%20scoparius">Convolvulus scoparius</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20amygdalina">Eucalyptus amygdalina</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name>
            </p>
